<p><img height="189" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Housing/Graphics/Dorm Header-26.png" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="451" /></p>
<hr />
<p>In Chapman Hall, each apartment has three bedrooms (six roommatres) along with a living room, bathroom, and closets in the hallway for  storage. Cooking facilities are not available at Chapman, but meal options can be arranged through <a href="http://www.byui.edu/foodservices/" target="_self">Food Services</a>.</p>
<hr />
<table border="0" cellpadding="10" style="width: 100%;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Amenities:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Twin XL bed 61" off the ground.&nbsp; Bed rail available upon request.</li>
<li>Mattress cover.</li>
<li>High efficiency closets - short and long hanging space and dresser  drawers for each person. Includes a place to apply makeup and style hair  with electrical outlets and mirrors.</li>
<li>One desk and chair per person.</li>
<li>Shelves in each bedroom.</li>
<li>Marker board in living room.</li>
<li>Ironing board and cover.</li>
<li>Microfridge&reg; (microwave and small fridge/freezer).</li>
<li>One sofa and one loveseat in the living room.</li>
<li>Vaccum, broom, dustpan, bucket, mirror, shower curtain, toilet brush, and plunger.</li>
<li>Coin-op laundry facilities.</li>
<li>High-speed wireless internet.</li>
<li>Satellite TV/DVD in main and upper lounges.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>Ping pong table, piano, and community kitchenette (for occasional use) in upper lounge</li>
</ul>
